headline.print_headline: Like Iran, Secret Diplomacy Leads to US-Cuba Thaw
headline.main: Like Iran, Secret Diplomacy Leads to US-Cuba Thaw

lead_paragraph: Fresh off his 2012 re-election victory, President Barack Obama summoned senior advisers to a series of meetings, asking them to "think big" about a second-term agenda that could include a new start with long-standing U.S. foes such as Iran and Cuba.
